The paper deals with algorithms in computer algebra, which involve the computation of power series solutions of ordinary differential equations over finite fields. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Symbolic Computation (cs.SC). The paper also discusses the issue of precision in computing the output accurately, which is a common concern in Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). The use of differential precision to obtain optimal bounds on the stability of the Newton iteration suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Dynamical Systems (cs.DS) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the applications of the results to manipulating algebraic numbers over finite fields, computing isogenies between elliptic curves, and finding roots of polynomials in finite fields suggest that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
